@JudiciaryDems When people are in government custody, we are responsible for their safety and well-being.

Pregnant women are some of the most vulnerable people in custody—and they’re receiving little to no medical care.

The Trump Administration’s cruelty and inhumanity know no bounds.

@JudiciaryDems Kash Patel gutted the unit investigating the 764 gang group—a nihilistic gang blackmailing kids to perform vile acts on camera.

Nearly every agent on the squad was reassigned to instead work on Stephen Miller’s personal agenda—arresting innocent, law-abiding immigrants.

Gross.

President Trump’s plan to support DHS agents at Naval Station Great Lakes is an act of political theater happening at the expense of Illinoisans’ wellbeing and tax dollars.
 
@SenDuckworth, @RepSchneider and I went to the base today and attempted to meet with DHS officials but were turned away.
 
What is DHS hiding from the American public?

@JudiciaryDems The Justice Department should hire the best of the best individuals to represent the United States.
 
Jared Wise doesn’t meet the standard.
 
He incited violence against law enforcement officers and belongs nowhere near DOJ.

@JudiciaryDems Targeting DACA holders who are LAWFULLY in the country and have committed NO crime is a terrible policy position.
 
No wonder the Trump Administration’s immigration approval ratings are tanking.
 
Secretary Noem needs to uphold DACA protections.

@JudiciaryDems The Second Circuit improperly restricted compassionate release, which district court judges can grant on a case-by-case basis.

This recent decision conflicts with the statute and runs afoul of Congress’s intent when we passed our landmark First Step Act.

It must be reversed.

@JudiciaryDems The Epstein case is a perfect example of how our justice system is NOT supposed to work.

The Justice Department is conducting backroom interviews with a proven liar and sex trafficker, Ghislaine Maxwell.

I’m putting the Deputy Attorney General on notice—no political games here.

@JudiciaryDems The Trump Administration is targeting immigrants who have done nothing wrong.

They are sending masked agents to arrest immigrants *following the rules* and showing up for court hearings.

None of it makes us safer.

Three years ago, the Supreme Court’s conservative supermajority opened the floodgates for draconian abortion restrictions.

The Dobbs decision created a health care crisis for women across the country.

@SenateDems will continue to fight for women’s rights.

We’ve made progress reducing the #1 cause of preventable death: smoking &amp; tobacco use. But Big Tobacco will keep trying to addict kids as new customers.

The @Surgeon_General found we must keep harmful, flavored tobacco products out of reach from kids.
@US_FDA: take note.
